center_name: Pediatric Diabetes Research Center, UCSD Stem Cell Program
description: Illumina HiSeq 2000 sequencing; Transcriptional and epigenetic profiling of the progression of hESCs to beta cells
experiment_title: Illumina HiSeq 2000 sequencing; Transcriptional and epigenetic profiling of the progression of hESCs to beta cells
library_construction_protocol: Strand-specific RNA-seq libraries were prepared as previously described [Parkhomchuk, D., et al., Nucleic Acids Res, 2009. 37:e123], with minor modifications. Following purification, mRNA was primed with Olig(dT)s and random hexamers, and reverse-transcribed to first-strand cDNA. Residual dNTPs were removed from the first-strand cDNA using Illustra MicroSpin G-25 columns (GE Healthcare). In the second-strand synthesis reaction, dUTPs were used instead of dTTPs. The converted double-strand cDNA was fragmented using a Bioruptor Sonicator for 60 cycles of 30 sec on and 30 sec off. After end-repair and adenine base addition, the cleaved double-strand cDNA fragments were ligated to Pair-end Adaptor Oligo Mix (Illumina) and size-fractionated on a 2% high resolution agarose gel (Sigma). cDNA fragments of 200 (+25 bp,-25bp) were recovered, and incubated with uracil-N-glycosylase (UNG) to digest the second-strand cDNA. Purified single-strand cDNA was then used as template for 15 cycles of amplification using pair-end PCR primers (Illumina). The amplified products were separated on a 2% agarose gel and a band between 225-275 bp excised.
sample_description: Protocols: CyT49 hESCs were maintained and differentiated as previously described [DAmour, K.A., et al., Nat Biotechnol, 2006. 24:1392-401; Kroon, E., et al., Nat Biotechnol, 2008. 26:443-52; Kelly, O.G., et al.,  Nat Biotechnol. 29:750-6]. Non-adherent conditions were applied to hESC differentiation. FACS isolation of late pancreatic endoderm (late PE) and polyhormonal cells (PH) was performed as previously described [Kelly, O.G., et al.,  Nat Biotechnol. 29:750-6]. hESC-derived hormone-producing cellular aggregates were enzymaticly dissociated to a single-cell suspension with Accumax (Innovative Cell Technologies) at 37 C for 20 min. Accumax was neutralized with FACS buffer (0.5%(wt/vol)BSA, 2 mM EDTA, PBS). Cells were then pelleted, resuspended in FACS buffer, and incubated with surface marker antibodies D200-APC (eBiosciences, 17-9200) and CD142-PE (BD Biosciences, 550312). FACS was performed on a FACSAria equipped with FACS DiVa software (BD Biosciences). Cells were sorted into PBS with 3% (vol/vol) FBS and pelleted for subsequent RNA-seq and ChIP-seq analysis. Briefly, cells were lysed in Trizol reagent (Invitrogen) for extraction of total RNA. Residual contaminating genomic DNA was removed using the Turbo Dnase kit (Ambion). mRNA was isolated from 2 ug of DNA-free total RNA using the Dynabeads mRNA Purification kit (Invitrogen). Strand-specific RNA-seq libraries were prepared as previously described [Parkhomchuk, D., et al., Nucleic Acids Res, 2009. 37:e123], with mino
cell_line_name: CD142+ late pancreatic endoderm from embryonic stem cell
study_title: Transcriptional and epigenetic profiling of the progression of hESCs to beta cells

Non-adherent conditions were applied to hESC differentiation. Transplantation of hESC-derived aggregates into severe combined immnuodeficient-beige mice and subsequent analyses of graft function were performed as described previously [Kroon, E., et al., Nat Biotechnol, 2008. 26:443-52; Kelly, O.G., et al.,  Nat Biotechnol. 29:750-6] with the minor modifications. Differentiated cellular aggregates were allowed to settle by gravity and loaded into semi-permeable macrocapsules (TheraCyte 20 ul device). The TheraCyte device has a pore size permeable to most proteins, but not cells. The diffusion properties of TheraCyte devices have been studied [Rafael, E., et al., Cell Transplant, 1999. 8:317-26]. Devices loaded with cells were inserted subcutaneously under anesthesia. 2 to 6 _ 106 cells were transplanted into each mouse. Enzyme-linked immunosorbent assays (Mercodia) were used to measure serum levels of human c-peptide before and 60 min after administration of glucose to mice. Grafts were harvested at 20-weeks after transplantation. Briefly, cells were lysed in Trizol reagent (Invitrogen) for extraction of total RNA. The amplified products were separated on a 2% agarose gel and a band between 225-275 bp excised.
